# Bieda TotalWar — git binary handling for Unreal Engine assets.
#
# WHY: with core.autocrlf=true (the default on Windows) and no rules here, git
# can apply line-ending / text normalisation to binary UE assets and CORRUPT
# them (.uasset/.umap deserialize errors: "Unexpected EOF", garbage offsets).
# Marking them "binary" = "-text -diff": git never converts or tries to merge
# them. This does NOT un-corrupt files already broken in history — it prevents
# any FUTURE damage on add / checkout / pull.

# ── Unreal Engine assets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.uasset  binary
*.umap    binary
*.ubulk   binary
*.uexp    binary
*.upk     binary
*.udk     binary

# ── Images / textures ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.bmp   binary
*.tga   binary
*.tif   binary
*.tiff  binary
*.exr   binary
*.hdr   binary
*.psd   binary

# ── Audio ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.wav   binary
*.ogg   binary
*.mp3   binary
*.flac  binary

# ── Models / fonts / misc binaries ──────────────────────────────────────────
*.fbx   binary
*.3ds   binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.icu   binary
*.bin   binary
*.dll   binary
*.lib   binary
*.pdb   binary
